Description
Sticky Notes

Objective:

To work with Bootstrap utilities, Flex design, and typography.

Concept Explanation:

Bootstrap Utilities: A set of pre-defined CSS classes for common tasks like spacing, alignment, and visibility control, allowing for rapid development and consistent styling across web projects.

Flex Design in Bootstrap: A powerful layout model that offers flexible and efficient ways to arrange elements within containers, enabling responsive designs that adapt to various screen sizes and orientations.

Typography in Bootstrap: Predefined styles and classes for text elements, ensuring consistent and visually appealing typography throughout the website, with options for headings, paragraphs, and other text styles.       

Concept Implementation:

Add the class and respective IDs to each sticky note. Utilize <h4> tags with Bootstrap contextual classes for headings and <p> tags for brief descriptions under each sticky note. Optionally, list tasks beneath each notice, and conclude by incorporating an <h1> tag with a plus sign within the <div> tag using Bootstrap classes.

Problem Description:

Create a sticky notes layout as depicted in the sample screenshot given below using Bootstrap and HTML components.

Requirements:

1.      The layout is given partially with a flex design. Add the class "notice" to all the five tasks like "Completed Tasks", "On Going Tasks", "Upcoming Tasks"  "Pending Tasks" and "Add New" as given in the sample screenshot with id as "job-1","job-2","job-3", "job-4" and "job-5" respectively. 

2.      Each sticky note is wrapped inside two div tags where the outer div tag should use the class "notice" (as mentioned above) and the inner div should call the respective bootstrap contextual class to reflect the background style as given in the sample screenshot. The inner div element should contain the <h4>, <p> and <ul> tags as mentioned in the point number 3, 4 and 5.

3.      Use <h4> to display the heading of each sticky note along with the respective bootstrap classes to represent the text color as white.

4.      Use <p> tag to display a small description under the heading for each notice as given in the sample screen.

5.      The tasks listed in each notice are optional.  You can create your own list of tasks.

6.      The <h1> tag, with its text centered, should be placed after the <h4> tag, with a plus sign inside the <div> element that has the ID 'job-5' (as shown in the screenshot).

